Steps 11–13 — Custom view, seed data, smoke test

Step 11 — Create the "Unresolved Org Units" view
In table editor → Views area → + New view.
Name:
Unresolved Org Units
Description:
Org Unit strings encountered by Flow 1 but not yet mapped to a Business Unit. Admin assigns Target BU to resolve.
Click Create. The view designer opens.
Columns to include (in this order):

Org Unit Variant
First Seen
Affected Records
Status
Target BU
Notes
Created On (system column — search "Created On" in the column picker)

Add each via the + View column button (or by dragging from the right-side column tree). Remove any default columns that aren't in the list above (typically just the primary column shows by default — you may need to remove "Created By" or similar).
Filters:
Click Edit filters (top of view designer).
Add filter:

Field: Status
Operator: Equals
Value: Unresolved

Sort:
Click Edit sort (or sort icon).

Sort by: First Seen
Direction: A → Z (ascending — oldest unresolved first)

Click Save and Publish at the top.

